headline: AI Jitters Spread to Commercial Real Estate
summary: Commercial real estate services firms this week have become one of the latest sectors to feel the stock market’s anxiety over artificial intelligence.  Shares of companies such as CBRE, Jones Lang LaSalle and Cushman & Wakefield fell sharply Wednesday and Thursday—down more than 25% for the two days—amid fears that AI could automate research, pricing analysis and deal sourcing.  Still, the AI concerns surfaced prominently on CBRE’s earnings call Thursday, even though the company reported record fourth-quarter revenue and double-digit earnings growth.
